The lobby of the hotel is warmly decorated and includes a cozy sitting area around a large fireplace.	They offer accessible rooms with showers, there is a ramp in the lobby, no steps to get into Hotel, and an elevator.	The hotel does have some quirks, but for a very old building in the heart of Montreal it is very nice.	It should be noted that the entire hotel only has ONE pc for internet access and it's in the lobby next to the valet, no privacy and sometimes you have to queue up to use it.	The lobby had a European charm, and the our room was very comfortable and modern-looking.